title: The Illustrated Guide to the Houses of America (Art Ebook)
description:
The Illustrated Guide to the Houses of America
Galahad Books | 1971 | ISBN: 0883651777 | English | 280 pages | PDF | 39.6 MB

From traditional Colonial to the house of the future, the remarkable diversity of American homes is displayed in hundreds of photographs selected especially for people who are dreaming about homes: buying, remodeling, restoring, or building them. This lavishly illustrated volume has been put together by some of the nation's leading architects. Each architect writes about the region in which he works. He discusses the architectural traditions of his area of the country, as well as its most modern home styles, and he presents a wide range of photographs and plans depicting regional home styling. Because each writer is a working architect, he can present the best of what is actually being built in America today, and he is thoroughly familiar with the requirements of real people for real homes
